    "Likewise, a study [G7] concluded that the participants of their study maintained responsibility as their specialised expertise not only enabled it but demanded it.",
    "A study [G8] reported 'responsibility' as an ethical principle that achieved the highest rank in terms of relevance in AI and it affected other ethical principles of AI.",
    "In this study, we use the terms 'responsibility' and 'accountability' interchangeably, following the definitions provided in Australia's AI ethics principles (See Appendix C for clarification).",
    "In a study [G5], the participants reported that they were also aware that they possessed sensitive customer data so they actively considered accountability in relation to cyber-security and data management.",
    "'Privacy' was another ethical principle that AI practitioners who participated in some studies were aware of and discussed widely."
